<!-- Course description -->
<hr>

<h2>Course Description</h2>

<p>The goal of this course is to provide students the necessary
conceptual background and hands-on experience to understand the most
common cryptographic algorithms and protocols and how to use them to
secure distributed applications and computer networks.</p>

<p><b>Prerequisites:</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>CS 0449, Introduction to Systems Software</li>
  <li>CS 1501, Algorithm Implementation</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Grading:</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>25% Midterm</li>
  <li>25% Final exam</li>
  <li>30% Projects</li>
  <li>10% Homeworks and in-class quizzes</li>
  <li>10% Attendence and participation</li>
</ul>


